title: Dirichlet's approximation theorem
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

For any real numbers $$\alpha \in \R$$ and $$N \ge 1$$ there exist integers $$p \in \Z$$ and $$q \in [1,N]$$ such that
$$
|q\alpha - p| \le \frac{1}{\lfloor N \rfloor + 1} < \frac{1}{N}.
$$